      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/api/main/utils/PolicyModelsProviderRetriever.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 56,
      "message": "sorry, now I'm remembering some details that I should have put in the JIRA: should only retry if it's a \"temporary\" issue, such as connectivity.  If it's a configuration issue (e.g., invalid host name, credentials), then it should not retry.  Not sure if there's a generic way to check for that; may have to include a list of retry-able connection codes in the config so they can be adjusted for the DBMS chosen by the organization.",
