      "id": "9817709b_27b6dc13",
      "file_path": "main/pom.xml",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 97,
      "message": "> change to mockito-all and remove the version\n\nmockito-all has not been updated since 2014 and pulls in old dependencies - e.g. hamcrest\nThis causes \"TestStatisticsReport.testStatisticsReport:45 » NoSuchMethod 'org.hamcrest.core...\"\nI can fix it by manually specifying hamcrest-core 1.3 in pom but can we not just use mockito-core?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7010,
        "name": "Gregory Hayes",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "gregory.hayes@est.tech",
        "username": "gregory.hayes"
      },
      "updated": "2020-11-24 08:40:09.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "e0c2c91e_729d2b54",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "fc5a5626_84e7c7fd",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/api/main/utils/PolicyModelsProviderRetriever.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 56,
      "message": "> sorry, now I'm remembering some details that I should have put in the JIRA: should only retry if it's a \"temporary\" issue, such as connectivity.  If it's a configuration issue (e.g., invalid host name, credentials), then it should not retry.  Not sure if there's a generic way to check for that; may have to include a list of retry-able connection codes in the config so they can be adjusted for the DBMS chosen by the organization.\n\nThis is problematic. There are no named exceptions thrown for connection failure by JPA. e.g. H2 and MariaDB use different exceptions. We can search for e.g. 'Connection refused' in getMessage() - which will work for H2 and MariaDB, but is fragile. As you suggest we can include search strings in config/params...",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7010,
        "name": "Gregory Hayes",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "gregory.hayes@est.tech",
        "username": "gregory.hayes"
      },
      "updated": "2020-11-24 08:40:09.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "e4735bdf_0cf92a46",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "160235e5_ac45ee0d",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/api/main/utils/PolicyModelsProviderRetriever.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 66,
      "message": "> for junit tests, we need a way to shorten this sleep to just a couple of milliseconds.  Some alternatives:\n> - make the retry period milliseconds instead of seconds\n> - wrap the Thread.sleep() call in a method and then override the method in the junit tests\n> - use CurrentTime object (from policy/common utils) to do sleep and override the object, in the junit tests, with a subclass of CurrentTime that simply returns when sleep is called\n\nWe can (manually) inject a mock CurrentTime object into the Retriever which will return immediately or throw InterruptedException",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7010,
        "name": "Gregory Hayes",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "gregory.hayes@est.tech",
        "username": "gregory.hayes"
