    {
      "id": "9f75117e_1e3fcc45",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/api/main/startstop/ApiDatabaseInitializer.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 91,
      "message": "If this method throws any exception, API will not come up. Maybe we should discuss how best to do this at the scrum.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2787,
        "name": "Liam Fallon",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "liam.fallon@est.tech",
        "username": "liamfallon"
      },
      "updated": "2020-11-30 12:15:22.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "ce7a8c97_640f189d",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/api/main/utils/PolicyModelsProviderRetriever.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 35,
      "message": "Yes, this should be an optional parameter with a default value. I think the current parameter handling can be used.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2787,
        "name": "Liam Fallon",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "liam.fallon@est.tech",
        "username": "liamfallon"
      },
      "updated": "2020-11-30 12:15:22.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "d1f19981_46d8108c",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/api/main/startstop/ApiDatabaseInitializer.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 91,
      "message": "I think it will be fine once the original lines 71 & 72 are restored and the connectWithRetry() method used instead.\n\nMy understanding of what the TSC said is that, on start-up:\n- for permanent errors (e.g., configuration issues), the pod should exit non-zero\n- for temporary errors (e.g., DB connectivity issues), the pod should keep retrying until the issue is resolved.  In particular, they're attempting to address the case where the DB pod comes up last.  In that case, the other pods should not exit, but should retry",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2020-11-30 18:43:22.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "9f75117e_1e3fcc45",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "3d7ff997_dd0e2eca",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/api/main/startstop/ApiDatabaseInitializer.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 91,
      "message": "As Liam mentioned, this could cause problems if the DB is intermittent. Should not getProvider and preLoadPolicies() be wrapped in their own retry loop (a DIY transaction) - which means moving the retry logic back here from Policy/Models?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7010,
        "name": "Gregory Hayes",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "gregory.hayes@est.tech",
        "username": "gregory.hayes"
      },
      "updated": "2020-11-30 20:59:03.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "d1f19981_46d8108c",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "d5c01ffc_e8b681be",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/api/main/startstop/ApiDatabaseInitializer.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 91,
      "message": "I don't really see the need to get into that level of error handling, particularly for something that will almost never occur.  Once we have a DB connection, it seems reasonable to assume it will remain available for the duration of the transaction, which is very short.\n\nIn any event, I'd still leave the retry logic in a common place; the developer can then decide which method is the appropriate one to use within the invoking code (though we'll probably only ever use the connectWithRetry method in initialization code).",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2020-11-30 21:09:44.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "3d7ff997_dd0e2eca",
      "unresolved": true
    },
